column5: We are headed up to LS the first week of Aug. Always get gas for the week at Intl Falls. Have heard that gas prices are a little cheaper south of the boarder. Can anyone give us some accurate info on prices at the Falls and say Brainerd Orr, etc etc. Thanks so much
I bought gas there Saturday (7/9) for $2.17/gallon. The cheapest place seemed to be that BP station outside of town a few miles.

Top of at the Murphy's station in Cloquet if you can, it's east of the 1st stoplight by wal mart. From there north the prices go right up, it was almost .30 more at Int Falls a week ago. Those guys know they got you this time of the year gas and diesel both.
has always been in Cook. Lunk
Last Sat. the 16th the price in the Falls was $2.29/gallon and the price in Dryden was $.90/liter
Here's a site you can use to check gas prices in Ontario and in the U.S. as well. http://www.ontariogasprices.com/inde...n&tme_limit=36 Have a great trip.
It was $2.16 at Murphy last night. $2.29 at most stations around Duluth. I woule expect about the same in the Cook/Orr area.

Hi. we find the best price at the food store/ gas station just west of the holiday inn in international falls its a big station so there is plenty of room to pull your boat and truck into and not too busy.
